04:02.636 --> 04:03.568
Who's Stan Wood?

04:03.570 --> 04:04.802
You know who Stan Wood is.

04:04.804 --> 04:06.903
He's the loud guy
at the Christmas party,

04:06.905 --> 04:08.404
you know, the guy who eats
all the meatballs,

04:08.406 --> 04:09.638
you know, and he has
the holiday cologne

04:09.640 --> 04:10.639
that smells like meatballs.

04:10.641 --> 04:11.806
You even call him Meatballs.

04:11.808 --> 04:15.143
Nice try, but I have a
mind like a steel trap.

04:15.145 --> 04:16.444
Except to clip
those nostril hairs.

04:16.446 --> 04:18.245
It's like staring up
at two tiny armpits.

04:18.247 --> 04:19.512
Listen, I'd love to bask

04:19.515 --> 04:20.880
in the shade
of Kilimanjaro here,

04:20.882 --> 04:21.981
but we have that thing.

04:21.983 --> 04:23.749
Oh, yeah, that thing, guys.

04:23.751 --> 04:24.815
That thing already?

04:24.817 --> 04:26.250
Oh, I know there's no thing.

04:26.252 --> 04:27.550
Wait, do I need
a sweater for the thing?

04:27.552 --> 04:29.251
Wait, ho-hold on,
this is not over.

04:29.253 --> 04:32.886
I should know about even our
most piddly, D-level client.

04:32.888 --> 04:34.120
D-level client?

04:34.122 --> 04:36.422
At Lewis, Roberts & Roberts
all our clients are A-level,

04:36.424 --> 04:37.890
